{"id": "c108_003", "pattern": "WWPDB AS CLEAREST BIPM-ANALOG (C108). The wwPDB combines mandatory deposition (enforced by journal policy for >200,000 structures), automated apparatus-computed validation for every deposit (Rfree/FSC/Ramachandran/clashscore), international consortium governance (US RCSB / EU PDBe / Japan PDBj / BMRB), permanent accession codes, and comprehensive reference archive. 'wwPDB for AI circuits' would require: mandatory deposition of model weights + circuit-level interpretability analysis + apparatus-computed validation (mechanistic consistency checks) for any published capability claim. This specifies the institutional architecture, not just the calibration standard (TMS analog from DC#6). The cryo-EM precedent: early high OA-DoF → near-zero OA-DoF via FSC + EMDB mandatory deposition — a trajectory AI interpretability could follow toward DC#3 full.", "category": "insight", "confidence": 0.85, "created": "2026-05-08T18:14:04+00:00"}
